This relationship indicates relatively severe constraints on the fidelity of magnetic data from Earth’s oldest rocks. For example, if rocks are heated to low-grade metamorphic conditions for 1 million years, a typical orogenic timescale, even single-domain magnetic grains with blocking temperatures \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
