$580^{\circ }$\end{document}C, the Curie temperature of magnetite [36] (Fig. 4n–o). The Barberton Mountains have seen lower-grade peak temperatures [52] than the JH Discovery Site and prior conglomerate tests attest to the preservations of high-unblocking-temperature magnetizations [53,54].

